HEADWORD: Huller
<hw>Hull"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, hulls; especially, an agricultural machine for removing the hulls
from grain; a hulling machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

